Section 4 — Data Exploration (EDA)

Explore dataset.

Examples:

df.info()
df.describe()
df.isnull().sum()

Visualizations:

Churn distribution
sns.countplot(x='Churn', data=df)

Insight:

Most customers do not churn, meaning the dataset is slightly imbalanced.

Contract vs Churn
sns.countplot(x='Contract', hue='Churn', data=df)

Insight:

Customers with month-to-month contracts churn significantly more.

Tenure vs Churn
sns.boxplot(x='Churn', y='tenure', data=df)

Insight:

Customers with shorter tenure have higher churn risk.

